6aa45ec5-438b-4ae7-bb3d-60766508c2d8.2067cafc-b53f-4604-84bc-c83e7f266515.prompt=Alternate Credentials - UserName\: 6aa45ec5-438b-4ae7-bb3d-60766508c2d8.32de2b94-8c25-4b4c-b28d-d0acb8f4d1d1.description=
Executes an Expression (e.x value1 \=\= value2)

Input Parameters\:
value1 - the value to threshold with
value2 - the threshold to threshold against
operator - (\=\=, \!\=,  >, >\=, <, <\=) the type of threshold
okstring - string to push into returnResult if the threshold has not been passed
failedstring - string to push into the returnResult if the threshold has been passed

Responses\:
True - the expression is true
Fales - the expression is false
6aa45ec5-438b-4ae7-bb3d-60766508c2d8.33df56e4-a6c8-4cc2-869d-36057b72cea5.description=Check the current date and time, and returns a java DateAndTime formatted string of it. Responses\: success - Date/time retrieved successfully. failure - Date/time could not be retrieved. 6aa45ec5-438b-4ae7-bb3d-60766508c2d8.43002b9b-b5b4-44fb-88ad-240f08b52ac8.prompt=Alternate Credentials - Password\: 6aa45ec5-438b-4ae7-bb3d-60766508c2d8.4a2fdc23-b584-4239-b9d6-8f324d55ad40.prompt=Alternate Credentials - Password\: 6aa45ec5-438b-4ae7-bb3d-60766508c2d8.4e3afb08-f9e2-408a-85b7-0ecc41010c1b.prompt=Mailbox User\: 6aa45ec5-438b-4ae7-bb3d-60766508c2d8.5a1167fe-4dbd-4dd0-b349-a2624b0b129f.prompt=Alternate Credentials - UserName\: 6aa45ec5-438b-4ae7-bb3d-60766508c2d8.68f740be-49cf-4a13-b546-c957d28f3347.description=
Finds the primary domain controller for a domain via DNS lookup.

Inputs\:
domain - The name of the domain to find the domain controller for.
dnsServer - The DNS server to query.

Responses\:
success - PDC retrieved.
failure - something went wrong.

Returns\:
The fully qualified host name of the PDC.
6aa45ec5-438b-4ae7-bb3d-60766508c2d8.6b3eecb4-f273-4acb-a874-6ae9f7e5a8f3.prompt=Enter a value for dnsServer 6aa45ec5-438b-4ae7-bb3d-60766508c2d8.72bcc878-ac42-4259-9881-7a9e72c91f90.prompt=Enter a value for domain 6aa45ec5-438b-4ae7-bb3d-60766508c2d8.88e4dfe3-a25b-40d0-85e3-4e57b7255b50.description=
Searches for a specific property in LDAP.  Returns the first result, stores the rest in a collection that is accessable via the LDAPSearchNextResult operation.

Input Parameters\:
Host - name or IP address of LDAP server to query
DN - base DN for search
Filter - search filter (ex. member\=CN\=User1,CN\=Users,DC\=mydomain,DC\=local)
PropertyName - name of property to return (ex. distinguishedName)
User - name of user to connect to LDAP as
Password - password of user

Responses\:
Ojbect(s) Retrieved - was able to retrieve objects from LDAP.  First value is returned as returnResult result
No Objects Found - either no objects where found or an error occurred.  See returnResult for more information
6aa45ec5-438b-4ae7-bb3d-60766508c2d8.b0bf955f-69df-4999-8b48-43aef0a00c9e.description=
Converts an string date time to an Active Directory Time Stamp (Integer8)

Input Parameters\:
adTimeStamp - string representation of the time stamp returned by ad

Responses\:
Passed - converted successfully (value is op result)
Failed - failed to convert
6aa45ec5-438b-4ae7-bb3d-60766508c2d8.dc91cb7e-1a39-4ba2-aee5-39f434520c09.prompt=DNSserver\: 6aa45ec5-438b-4ae7-bb3d-60766508c2d8.description=
Finds the primary domain controller for a domain via DNS lookup and checks to see if an account is locked.

Inputs\:
    domain - The name of the domain whose domain controller you want to find
    dnsServer - The DNS server to query
    mbuser - The name of the user whose mailbox is checked
    altuser - The username to use when authenticating with the host
    altpass - The password for altuser

Responses\:
    success - The operation completed as stated in the description
    failure - The operation completed unsuccessfully
